title: Clean cash - Installation
text: Step 1: Log in to DdDPOS using Clerk number Step 2: Open DdDAdmin (Upper right-hand side of the UI) Step 3: Chose klient and machine and press "Change this machine" Step 4: Scroll down to "Advanced configuration" and type in the password: dddpos+2016 Step 5: Find "Use cleancash" Step 6: Set value to 1 Step 7: Remember to hit save before closing the program Step 8: Reload the terminal - Write reload in the Clerk ID field Step 9: Close the terminal - Clerk 999 and password 0 Step 10: Open C: drive on the PC Step 11: POS -> Program -> Bin -> Debug Step 12: Find following programs CleanCashAPISetup.msi CleanCashAPISetup_1_1_PA7.msi CleanCashUpdate.exe Step 13: Run CleanCashAPISetup.msi - Hit next until it starts installing Step 14: Run CleanCashAPISetup_1_1_PA7.msi - Hit next until it starts installing Step 15: Run CleanCashUpdate.exe - It just opens a black screen quickly Step 16: Go to C: -> POS -> Program -> Bin -> Debug -> Printer -> Configuration -> Esc Koder.ini Step 17: Find [cleancashconfig] Step 18: Set Post=COM1 Step 19: Test if it works by making a sale on a random item group and 1 kr. You should get an extra receipt from the sale, which shows that the cleancash is active. Step 20: Make a return of the sale.
description:
Step 1: Log in to DdDPOS using Clerk number 

Step 2: Open DdDAdmin (Upper right-hand side of the UI)  

 

  

Step 3: Chose klient and machine and press "Change this machine" 

  

 

  

Step 4: Scroll down to "Advanced configuration" and type in the password: dddpos+2016 

 

 

  

Step 5: Find "Use cleancash" 

Step 6: Set value to 1 

Step 7: Remember to hit save before closing the program 

  

 

Step 8: Reload the terminal - Write reload in the Clerk ID field 

Step 9: Close the terminal - Clerk 999 and password 0 

 

Step 10: Open C: drive on the PC 

Step 11: POS -> Program -> Bin -> Debug 

Step 12: Find following programs 

  1. CleanCashAPISetup.msi 

  1. CleanCashAPISetup_1_1_PA7.msi 

  1. CleanCashUpdate.exe 

Step 13: Run CleanCashAPISetup.msi - Hit next until it starts installing 

Step 14: Run CleanCashAPISetup_1_1_PA7.msi - Hit next until it starts installing 

Step 15: Run CleanCashUpdate.exe - It just opens a black screen quickly 

 

Step 16: Go to C: -> POS -> Program -> Bin -> Debug -> Printer -> Configuration -> Esc Koder.ini 

 

Step 17: Find [cleancashconfig]  

Step 18: Set Post=COM1 

 

Step 19: Test if it works by making a sale on a random item group and 1 kr. 

You should get an extra receipt from the sale, which shows that the cleancash is active. 

Step 20: Make a return of the sale.

title: Clean Cash - won't connect (Swedish customers)
text: CleanCash won't connect OBS! First find out, which com-port the CleanCash box is connected to (COM1/COM2 etc.) Ask the customer to check. Open POS Click on Screen w/wrench Go to Advanced Configuration (pw is always DDD+2016 to unlock greyed out fields) Find UseCleanCash and set it to 0 Scroll down to the bottom of the page and click Save Shut down the POS program (enter 999 in the Sales Asisstant field, use 70223010 as password) In Windows Explorer, open POS/Program/bin/Debug/Printer/Configuration/ESC Koder.txt Scroll down to [CleanCashConfig] Change Port (if different from what it says in ESC Koder.txt) Save Ask customer to turn off / unplug the CleanCash box and leave it off for 30-60 seconds. Then turn on / plug back in. 1. Start POS 2. Go to Advanced Configuration 3. Find UseCleanCash and set it to 1 4. Save 5. Restart POS In most cases, this will work. If it doesn't, there could be an issue with CleanCash in general and they will have to wait for it to be cleared. This usually means that you will get calls from other customers as well about it. If it is a big issue for them and they cannot wait, you can temporarily turn off the use of CleanCash by following the above steps to set it to 0. This is not advisable, though.
description:
CleanCash won't connect 

  

OBS! First find out, which com-port the CleanCash box is connected to (COM1/COM2 etc.) Ask the customer to check. 

  

  1. Open POS 

  1. Click on Screen w/wrench 

 

  

  1. Go to Advanced Configuration (pw is always DDD+2016 to unlock greyed out fields) 

  

 

  

  1. Find UseCleanCash and set it to 0 

  

 

  

  1. Scroll down to the bottom of the page and click Save 

  

 

  

  

Shut down the POS program (enter 999 in the Sales Asisstant field, use 70223010 as password) 

  

  1. In Windows Explorer, open POS/Program/bin/Debug/Printer/Configuration/ESC Koder.txt 

  1. Scroll down to [CleanCashConfig] 

  1. Change Port (if different from what it says in ESC Koder.txt) 

  1. Save 

  

 

  

Ask customer to turn off / unplug the CleanCash box and leave it off for 30-60 seconds. Then turn on / plug back in. 

  

  1. 1. Start POS 

  1. 2. Go to Advanced Configuration 

  1. 3. Find UseCleanCash and set it to 1 

  1. 4. Save 

  1. 5. Restart POS 

  

In most cases, this will work. If it doesn't, there could be an issue with CleanCash in general and they will have to wait for it to be cleared. This usually means that you will get calls from other customers as well about it. 

  

If it is a big issue for them and they cannot wait, you can temporarily turn off the use of CleanCash by following the above steps to set it to 0. This is not advisable, though.
